@Node introduction

There are several Charts out in the scene at this moment. The reason that
we decided to release one of our own, was that we didn't feel that there
was a Complete chart over the Scene to be found anywhere.
The charts out covered either a very limited amount of boards, or were just
including boards from a specified area of the country. We will try to 
include ALL boards in sweden. In that way we hope to get a FAIR chart
over the scene.

This was not accomplished in the first issue, since we "only" cover 38 
boards. We are hoping to have all Swedish Elite boards in the Dreamcharts
withing 1 or 2 issues.

There Is a story behind the making of The Dream Charts. It's not an intere-
sting story, but I'll tell It anyways. It all began some 4 months ago, when
I got the idea of making a HALLANDSTOPPEN chart. I called up one of my 
friends BIZTRO, sysop at REALM OF CHAOS, and got into chat. 
He told me that he had plans to make a chart of some kind, that would 
include all boards In HALLAND. Coincidence or What?!
Since we both had the same plans, we decided to join and make the chart
together. No use in having 2 charts over the same area. At that time
SVERIGETOPPEN was (and still is) Very popular. But I've got pissed at
every release, seeing a list of the "best traders in sweden", where 
people that have traded 300mb were included, and where I with about 1 
gig at the time, was excluded. That is NOT what i call SVERIGEtoppen,
but 19-boards-in-sweden-toppen. 
So I called up Biztro and said, No way man, the scene doesn't need a 
HALLANDSchart, it needs a complete SWEDENchart, and I mean Complete!
Said and done, we decided to make a BIG chart. This was by no way an
easy task. I called up VILEIUS and told him of our plans. As usual he
was full of great ideas and suggestions. The three of us worked on the
DREAM CHARTS for some 3 months, and it is that work you now hold in your
hands. Happy reading!

@endnode

@node future plans

Our highest priority right now, is to have all boards in sweden included.
Once this is done and the Dream Charts get's established we will maybe
turn our eyes outwards, towards Europe and the States.
It would be a fun thing, comparing the swedish traders with the traders
of the world. Anyhow, you don't need to think about that YET. When the
time comes we will have a vote about it.

Talking about VOTE. As you will notice, there are no Vote's in this
issue. We have TANGO/DPL and VILEIUS/IND working on a Vote door.
Tango is doing his military service so I suppose we will start out by 
Using Vileius door as soon as It's ready.

We are also working on a door that will count the ACTUAL SPEED of the 
Boards. HOW? you ask... Well, we will check out all the majors released
each month. We will then take a look and see exactly when the Boards got
the Majors ul'ed. Points will be given, and we will have a more accurate
speed chart than one based on only the amount of ul/dl.
As an example: If HYSTERIA get's all the majors 2 days before any other
BBS in Sweden, then hysteria IS the fastest board, even though there 
are boards that have more traded gig's, and therefore is in a higher
position at the BOARDS chart.

We'd also like to include a TOP GROUPS list, but at the moment that is
impossible, since there are so many variations in writing your locations,
and there are so many account's, that a manual calculation would take
several days. Also, many traders have not their group in their location, 
but have other quite meaningless statements. A door to solve this problem
will be released.

Those are SOME of the future plans, but there are many, many more. And
I'm sure we will get some intresting suggestions from the people in the
scene. Just call our HQ's and leave me a mail.
@endnode

