@node	vs_notes "        About the charts and the calculations:"

An 'I' to the right stands for inactive this month.

A trader need 256kb up or down on a board to be counted, a total of 50 Mb
upload to appear in the chart. Spelling of handle and location is taken
from the board which have received most wares.

Boards will also have users below 256kb counted.

All charts are sorted by kb rather than Mb's so if boards/users have the
same Mb's in a chart and different positions these will still be correct.

Since everything is kept in kb's as far as possible, a total count will
be correct even if it's higher than the entries total.

One Mb is of course one real Mb, since it's easier to calc bitwise.

Matching is made with a pseudo-intelligent routine, if you've found
that some of your accounts haven't been counted it's because you have
such a fucked up spelling of your handle at that board. Shared accounts
are treated seperately from those sharing, i.e a+b/a/b are three users.

A grouplist should also be generated, but at this time it's not realistic
to match all more or less creative locations (if it's the groupname at all).

 / VILEIUS

