@Node Scene_Talk
                          DALAMAR 04-11-94 14:45

I really have much to do, getting this Chart ready, But I feel that I
would like to have some sort of article included anyhow. Don't expect
to much from this one.

I'd like to say a few words about some things in the modem scene. First
I'll ask you all a question: Is there really a need for "Walls"?
I don't know about you, but I'M sure as hell getting tired of reading
stuff like "Vit Makt - NegerSlakt", "Xxxxx Is a Fucking Lamer",
"Call +Xx-xx-xxxx", "Suck My dick", "Rösta Ja till EU", "Rösta Nej Till
EU", "SIEG HEIL"osv.osv. The only thing I've seen that this have led to, Is
that a lot Of people become enemies. Then we have this category that fakes
the userhandle, and leaves some lame message, and by that way pisses many
people off and leaves place for missunderstandings between users.
In my opinion, there IS a messagebase. If people have something important
to say, they can leave an EALL, or if they want to start an discussion
they can leave an ALL.

Another thing I question Is the Need of New User Passwords. If there IS
any need for them at all, that means. I suppose the idea of the whole thing
Is to prevent those that are not "elite" enuff, from logging on to the
system. But It also prevents those who ARE "elite" enuff from entering.
A trader that spends all his spare time trading, selldom has time to start
searching for NUP's. Sure, He can leave a mess at some known BBS and w8
for an answer, but It's selldom that anyone has the current NUP, or has
the energy to call and check with the sysop. Or he just forgets about it.

Anyhow, any lamer can get a NUP, If he tries hard enuff. It's no guarantee
that a person is a good trader, just becoz he got hold of the NUP. In my
opinion the selection of which users should be validated or not, should
be made on basis of TempAns and/or a Voice validation.
So if you don't want lamers, you could just delete them. You can do like
JUAN at ASYLUM, when a new User applies for an account, he leaves an EALL
and asks if any of his users has any info on him.
Or you could have a door that let's the new User leave a message for you,
but without letting him into the system at all... there are many various
ways of dealing with this, and still leave the door open for those traders
that deserve to be on the board, but that can't spend time & money searching
for NUP's.

Another thing that crosses my mind are Ratios. The most common ratio should
be 1:3  That means that the sysop allows the user to download 3 times as
much as he uploads. That IS the deal. Now..how comes all sysop's become
hysteric when a user reaches 1:2 ? or even 1:1? Sysop's can't seriously
demand that a user ONLY should upload, and never download. That's not the
way trading works.
Many Users get a warning or make the sysop irritated bcoz they "only" have
uploaded 200mb while they have leeched 450mb... So what? The Sysop HAS
given them a 1:3 ratio. For those sysops that think that a trader should
stick around 1:1 or maybe 1:0, they should give their users THAT ratio
instead!!  They have no right complaining or lowering the ratios AFTERWARD.

The speed of a bbs is not after all counted only by the amount of the Ul's
made, Dl's made Is a factor that is just as important. It's very easy to
Ul lots of megz at a slow bbs, but no one leeches it, if it is so slow it
ain't worth trading. (except the pay-users that is...)

Just to give an example, I traded at a bbs, let's just call it THE BBS.
I reached about 210mb up / 45mb down, and was about to get a major, when
the sysop breaks into chat and starts talking about me beeing a leech,
about how a user that "only leeches" and doesn't ul accordingly should be
deleted, about why I ul'ed that file there, but not here and so on...
Some times when I marked files and took "d" without Ul'ing first, I was
Kicked. And it was a Multinode-system, so I didn't block anyone out by
dl'n. Some kind of GESTAPO or what?. and still I was, accourding to the ratio
he had given me, allowed to download another 585mb. Not that I would, but
I'm only trying to tell all the sysops to set the ratios the way they like
it, and then Stop Complaining about it.

Finnaly, lets say a word or two about credits. It's kinda unfair that some
BBS's gives away *2 or *3 on majors, Snes, etc. Or, It's NOT unfair as long
as it folows the rules. And I hope that all sysops know how it works.
You can give away *2 on majors if you want, but only if you have CREDS enuff
to give away. From Deleted Users etc. I will not explain this in detail,
but I can say that a lot of sysops are "cheating". Sure, I can announce
a compo with 5GIG in prices, and I can Give *10 creds on all files Ul'ed,
But that would not be fair, would it? It's all FAKE creds.
The same way Sweden can't just press a lot of money to pay the Debt the
country has, bcoz of inflation and so on. It works the same way In cyber-
space. The are standards and rules to be followed.

Well, anyhow, I cannot continue this article because there are other more
important things to do. Now, Don't you think I'm totaly negative to
everything just because i "complain" in this Article. The reason Is that
I'm trying to start a debate. So.. If anyone has something to say about
this article, or wants to write a article for the DreamCharts himself,
he can just login to one of our HQ's. There Is a Dream Charts Conference
where people can leave Ideas, Articles, Replys, dl old Dreamcharts issues
or do whatever they like in, as long as it is connected with the chart
in any way.
Ok guys, that's all from me, Next time I'll try to include some funnier
articles, maybe someone sends me some good ones, but in this issue we really
didn't have the time doing nice articles. Hope I didn't bore you too much.
@endnode

